\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Overview of the CausalRAG Architecture.} The system consists of two main stages: (1) A \textit  {Retrieval System} that enhances standard hybrid search (BM25 + Dense) with domain-specific causal graph extraction to boost causally relevant evidence. (2) A \textit  {Reasoning System} based on Qwen2.5-32B fine-tuned with Extended LoRA, which processes the retrieved context to predict the most plausible causes via a multi-label classification head.}}{3}{figure.caption.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:system}{{3}{3}{\textbf {Overview of the CausalRAG Architecture.} The system consists of two main stages: (1) A \textit {Retrieval System} that enhances standard hybrid search (BM25 + Dense) with domain-specific causal graph extraction to boost causally relevant evidence. (2) A \textit {Reasoning System} based on Qwen2.5-32B fine-tuned with Extended LoRA, which processes the retrieved context to predict the most plausible causes via a multi-label classification head}{figure.caption.4}{}}
